    affiliation: "Baylor College of Medicine"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-05-23"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/samersalman/scifield"
url: "https://github.com/samersalman/scifield"
abstract: >
  SciField is a multi-axis framework for monitoring the health of a scientific
  field. It builds a longitudinal corpus from a defined set of journals,
  enriches each article with thematic, epistemic, and novelty signals, and
  uses those signals to forecast where a field is headed. Release v0.1.0
  ships the corpus harvester, enrichment pipeline (OpenAlex / Semantic Scholar /
  ROR / author disambiguation), embedding bake-off, FAISS HNSW index, BERTopic
  thematic backbone (V1-S06), and the epistemic-extraction scaffolding (V1-S07)
  with its OSF pre-registration #1.
